dies and poststructural theory, exploring and clarifying the films' uneasy tension between class and gender, and their explorations of fractured temporality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh  aJoseph Losey.  aMarxism.  aModernism.  aSoviet ideological model.  aStalin's policies.  ablatant economic necessity.  aequal footing.  afear of betrayal.  apolitical commitment.  aprogressive realism.  apublic tolerance.  atax exile.  atax problems.1 aGardner, Colin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614156940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141569423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141569/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles